summary: The document is an identification form related to the JFK Assassination System, dated 01/14/98, and appears to be part of a series of records concerning DOD-affiliated personnel incident investigations. It details Manuel Marti, a private in the US Army, including his education at Theodore Roosevelt Night High School and Bronx Community College, along with personal details such as date and place of birth, and previous addresses. The document also mentions an agent report and includes a control symbol or file number, indicating its role in a larger investigative or administrative process. Marked 'FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY', it underscores the document's sensitive nature.
key_findings: The document is part of the JFK Assassination System records, suggesting a connection to investigations surrounding the assassination.
Manuel Marti's educational and personal details are recorded, including his attendance at Theodore Roosevelt Night High School and Bronx Community College.
